nt-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">1. Read the value in PROCHOT_RESPONSE_POWER</span><br /><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">2. Assert Prochot using&nbsp;global_prochot_hw_inject = 0x1</span><br /><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">3. Verify the power is reduced to the value in step 1</span><br /><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">4. Repeat with different values&nbsp;</span><h4>Configuration *</h4>\nHow does the platform need to be configured to obtain the desired coverage? For example: fuses, bios knobs, pre-test scripts, kernel/OS config. In the case of BIOS knobs, list all that impact this coverage, including both custom and default.<br /><br /><h4>Pass/Fail criteria *</h4>\nExamples: register values to look for, what content output to look for on the screen, key words or sections in the log.<br /><br /><h4>Intent Verification Strategy *</h4>\nHow will TC logic be checked out prior to testing on silicon (e.g. on N-1 hardware, in Simics, etc.)?  If not possible, explain why (e.g. new feature not present in N-1 and not modelled in pre-si environment).<br /><br /><h4>HW Requirements</h4>\nWhat besides silicon is required for execution of this test?  For example: logic analyzer, a thermal head, an Intel test card or IHV device, etc.<br /><br /><h4>SW Requirements</h4>\nWhat software besides actual test content is needed for execution of this test?  For example: special version of operating system, drivers, firmware, or harassers (to run with the main test content), software tool(s).<br /><br /><h4>Coverage</h4>\nSpecify any expected coverage that is dependent on environment or configuration (not covered in the TCD's description).  Also specify any coverage assessment/measurement technique that might be used, if applicable and if not stated in the TCD.<br /><br /><h4>Component Interactions</h4>\nDescribe or illustrate the components that are involved and how they interact. This section is only needed if it provides more information than the TCD article, perhaps specific to the validation environment and framework used for this test_case.<br /><br />",
